# Node.js Docker Standards

## Base Image Selection

- **Production**: Use `node:20-alpine` (small, secure)
- **Development**: Use `node:20-slim` if Alpine compatibility issues arise

## Multi-Stage Dockerfile Pattern

```dockerfile
# Build stage
FROM node:20-alpine AS builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm ci --only=production

# Runtime stage
FROM node:20-alpine
WORKDIR /app

# Create non-root user
RUN addgroup -g 1001 -S app && adduser -S -u 1001 app -G app
USER app

# Copy dependencies and app
COPY --from=builder --chown=app:app /app/node_modules ./node_modules
COPY --chown=app:app . .

ENV NODE_ENV=production
EXPOSE 3000

HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \
  CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:3000/health || exit 1

CMD ["node", "dist/server.js"]
```

## Key Node-Specific Settings

### Environment Variables

```dockerfile
# Set production mode
ENV NODE_ENV=production

# Disable npm update check
ENV NPM_CONFIG_UPDATE_NOTIFIER=false
```

### Health Check (Alpine-compatible)

```dockerfile
# Using wget (available in alpine)
HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \
  CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:3000/health || exit 1
```

### npm vs yarn vs pnpm

**npm:**

```dockerfile
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm ci --only=production
```

**yarn:**

```dockerfile
COPY package.json yarn.lock ./
RUN yarn install --frozen-lockfile --production
```

**pnpm:**

```dockerfile
RUN npm install -g pnpm
COPY package.json pnpm-lock.yaml ./
RUN pnpm install --frozen-lockfile --prod
```

### Framework-Specific CMD

**Express/Fastify:**

```dockerfile
CMD ["node", "dist/server.js"]
```

**NestJS:**

```dockerfile
CMD ["node", "dist/main.js"]
```

**With TypeScript (ts-node in dev):**

```dockerfile
# Production: compiled JS
CMD ["node", "dist/server.js"]

# Development: ts-node
CMD ["npx", "ts-node", "src/server.ts"]
```

